# Cuties Team Charter
This is our team charter, which contains our team's rules and standards. Create a signed copy of this document in `admin/misc/rules-studentname.pdf`. See the folder for an example

## 1. Purpose and Objectives
- Improve individual technical skills
- Learn how to properly leverage novel AI tools
- Gain exposure to what it's like to work in an organized software engineering environment

## 2. Common Values and Standards
- Don't hesitate to ask questions or seek help
- Provide constructive criticism without any personal attacks or insults
- Keep an open mind, especially when it comes to collaboration
- Be respectful to everyone on the team

## 3. Roles and Responsibilities
- Team Lead / Project Manager: Yuval and Jordan
- Note Taker: Roy
- Github / Repo Admin: Angelo and Bowen
- Fullstack Lead: Koji
- Frontend Leads: Harvey and Jenny
- Backend Leads: Alec and Angelo
- QA / Testing Lead: Roy and Alec
- Design Lead: Fariba

Note: These roles do not strictly limit what you can/will work on

## 4. Conflict Resolution
- Try to handle conflicts individually first, but make sure it never gets personal. Try to comrpomise
- If the conflict further escalates, contact team leads (Yuval + Jordan)
- If unable to be resolved with team leads, bring in TA (Omair)

## 5. Communication Protocols
- <24 hour response time on Slack
- Notify team leads at least 24 hours in advance if you cannot make it to a meeting
- Try to communicate clearly and openly to teammates
- All official business should be discussed on Slack

